```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Int = 3)
    return dt + Millisecond(bump * 60 * 1000))
end

function timezone_bumper(dt::Date, bump::Int = 3)
    throw(error("Cannot bump a Date type. Use DateTime instead."))
end
```

The function `timezone_bumper` accepts a `DateTime` object and an optional integer `bump` which defaults to 3 if not provided. It then returns a new `DateTime` object with the specified number of hours added.

If a `Date` object is passed, it throws an error indicating that only `DateTime` types can be bumped.
